                            <comment id="13993444" author="krummas" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 07:01:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;nit, i guess we can remove the &quot;if(cfStore == null)&quot; check in getValidColumnFamilies since keyspace.getColumnFamilyStore(..) will never return null&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13995300" author="yukim" created="Mon, 12 May 2014 17:39:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, with suggested nit fixed. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13995630" author="mshuler" created="Mon, 12 May 2014 21:06:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This commit broke repair functionality.  The repair_test.py dtest hangs after this commit, and watching the ccm node system logs while running locally shows no activity on any of the nodes after the repair command is run. No errors, just no repair..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13995702" author="yukim" created="Mon, 12 May 2014 22:04:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mshuler&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mshuler&quot;&gt;mshuler&lt;/a&gt; I pushed the fix in 3fab711ee76c081c0ab5874d64b78673334f9071 to fix repair hang when no CF names are given.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13995848" author="mshuler" created="Tue, 13 May 2014 00:12:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=yukim&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;yukim&quot;&gt;yukim&lt;/a&gt;, repair_test runs fine on 2.1/trunk again  &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
